The paper discusses parameter tuning in the context of multi-objective temporal planning using evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of meta-optimization methods such as ParamILS suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of a specific evolutionary planner (DaE-YAHSP), which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses issues related to software engineering (cs.SE) in the context of parameter tuning.
